## Gate (`pr_gate`)

- Block correctness bugs and security-relevant defects in the PR diff.
- Dependency policy applies to **changed** pins / lockfile entries only for
  **enabled ecosystems**.
- Apply quarantine, holds, grouping, and bundles on those changes.
- Verdict only: follow [`change-review.md`](library/gate/change-review.md) and
  [`scenarios/gate.md`](library/scenarios/gate.md). No Issues / fix PRs from gate.

## Maintain (`main_maintain`)

- Scan the full repo for enabled ecosystems and hotspots below.
- Enforce the **same** quarantine approach and duration as gate.
- Open Issues per [[`findings.md`](../maintain/findings.md)](library/maintain/findings.md); fix PR per
  [`pr-lifecycle.md`](library/maintain/pr-lifecycle.md) when [`verify.md`](../../../../verify.md) passes.
- Reconcile against **this checkout only**.
- Never APPROVE product pull requests.
- Procedure: [`../scenarios/maintain.md`](../scenarios/maintain.md).

## Hotspots (edit for this product)

- List primary source trees and manifests the agent should prioritize.

## Overrides

See [[`holds.md`](../policy/holds.md)](library/policy/holds.md). Explicit accepted-risk comments may clear
**non-critical** gate findings; critical and policy FORBIDDEN states need a
documented exception.
